Whether speaker diarization should be enabled for this conversation. Pass this as true to enable speaker separation. Use this parameter to auto-detect multiple voices in the same audio file. queryParams.description: Enter a non-negative integer to specify the number of conversations to return. For example, if you have processed more than 3 conversations and enter 3, the response returns 3 conversations.
Enter a non-negative number of items to skip before applying the limit.
Specify the sort order for results based on start time. Choose for asc ascending order or desc for descending order.

Set the start of the startTime range for conversations to be returned. The startTime is read from the Conversation entity. If you do not provide a value, the default range is the previous 7 days. The startTime value must be formatted in ISO 8601 format. For example 2020-07-10 15:00:00.000 is the 10th of July 2020 at 3 PM. The value must be less than the current time and less than the endTime of conversations to be returned.

Specify the end of the date time range for conversations to be returned. The endTime is read from the Conversation entity. If you do not provide a value, the current timestamp is the default endTime. The endTime value must be formatted in ISO 8601 format. The value must be less than current timestamp and greater than startTime of conversations to be returned.
Specify one or more fields to be used to sort the results.

Enter a filter string in RSQL format. This parameter accepts all RSQL logical operator except OR. There is no limit on the number of filters, but each filter can only have two parameters separated by a logical operator. For example conversation.endDate <= 2022-07-15 12:00:00.000. Default is conversation.startDate <= {currentTimestamp - 7 days}.
